task_description: Facing the building to your North-East (approx. 42°), estimate the height of the main building in front of you in meters. Answer with one number and a short rationale.

reason: Moving right (10 meters) will provide a better vantage point to view the entire height of the target building, ensuring I can see both the ground level and the roof for an accurate height estimate.

Repeated left rotations haven't reoriented me toward the target; moving back (MOVE(2)) will return me to the prior position where I was facing the North-East target building, allowing me to locate it for height estimation.
Based on the visual of the large domed building in the distance, I estimate its height to be approximately 18 meters, as it appears to be a 6-story structure with each story averaging 3 meters.
